## 16. Environment Setup (Zero to Running)

```bash
# 1. Create project from scratch
npm create vite@latest ./ -- --template react
# (Run this inside the c:\echoRoots_webapp directory)

# 2. Install core dependencies
npm install react-router-dom zustand framer-motion
npm install firebase
npm install @google/generative-ai

# 3. Install Tailwind CSS (v4 with Vite plugin)
npm install -D tailwindcss @tailwindcss/vite

# 4. Configure Vite for Tailwind (vite.config.js)
# Add @tailwindcss/vite plugin вҖ” see file structure section

# 5. Set up CSS entry (src/index.css)
# Add: @import "tailwindcss";

# 6. TalkingHead setup
# Download from: https://github.com/met4citizen/TalkingHead
# Copy talkinghead.mjs + modules/ directory to public/talkinghead/

# 7. Ready Player Me avatar
# Go to https://readyplayer.me вҶ’ Create elder character вҶ’ Export GLB
# Download URL with: ?morphTargets=ARKit,Oculus+Visemes&textureAtlas=1024
# Save to: public/models/elder-avatar.glb

# 8. Mixamo animations
# Go to https://www.mixamo.com
# Search: "Idle", "Talking", "Greeting"
# Download each as FBX вҶ’ Save to public/animations/

# 9. Create .env file
# VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_here
# VITE_ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=your_key_here
# VITE_ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=your_voice_id_here

# 10. Firebase setup
# Create project at https://console.firebase.google.com
# Enable: Firestore Database, Firebase Storage
# Copy web app config to src/services/firebase.js
# Create Firestore vector index for knowledge_base collection

# 11. Start development
npm run dev
```

